HLD (High-Level Design) 
Title: RAG-Based Customer Support Assistant (HLD)
1. System Overview

This system is a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) based customer support assistant.
It retrieves information from a PDF knowledge base and generates context-aware answers.
It also supports Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) for complex queries.

2. Architecture

User → Interface → LangGraph Workflow → Retriever → Vector Database → LLM → Response
↘ HITL (if needed)

3. Components
Document Loader (PDF input)
Chunking Module
Embedding Model (HuggingFace)
Vector Database (ChromaDB)
Retriever
LLM (Groq)
LangGraph Workflow
HITL Module
4. Data Flow

PDF → Chunk → Embed → Store in DB
User Query → Retrieve relevant chunks → Generate answer → Confidence check → Output / HITL

5. Technology Choices
LangChain → pipeline
LangGraph → workflow control
ChromaDB → vector storage
HuggingFace → embeddings
Groq → fast LLM
6. Scalability
Chunking handles large PDFs
Retrieval optimized with vector search
Can scale to multiple documents